It seems like the issue is that I'm trying to print the XML output directly to the console, which doesn't work as expected.

Instead, I'll modify the code to write the XML output to a file. Here's an updated version of the Java class:
```java
import org.json.JSONObject;
import org.json.JsonParser;

public class MissionPlanGenerator {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        // Load GeoJSON file
        String geoJsonFile = "path/to/geojson/file.geojson";
        JSONObject geoJsonData = new JSONObject(new JsonParser().parse(geoJsonFile));

        // Generate XML file
        generateXml(geoJsonData, "output.xml");
    }

    public static void generateXml(JSONObject geoJsonData) throws Exception {
        // Create XML output stream
        java.io.FileWriter writer = new java.io.FileWriter("output.xml");

        // Write XML header
        writer.write("<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n");

        // Write root element
        writer.write("<MissionPlan>\n");

        // Add CompositeTaskInformation element
        writer.write("  <CompositeTaskInformation>\n");

        // Add task elements
        for (int i = 0; i < geoJsonData.getJSONArray("features").length(); i++) {
            JSONObject feature = geoJsonData.getJSONArray("features").getJSONObject(i);
            writer.write("    <Task>\n");
            writer.write("      <Name>" + feature.getString("properties.name") + "</Name>\n");
            writer.write("      <Description>" + feature.getString("properties.description") + "</Description>\n");
            writer.write("    </Task>\n");
        }

        // Close CompositeTaskInformation element
        writer.write("  </CompositeTaskInformation>\n");

        // Close root element
        writer.write("</MissionPlan>\n");

        // Flush output stream
        writer.close();
    }
}
```
This version of the Java class writes the XML output to a file named "output.xml". You can modify the filename as needed.

Please note that this code still assumes that you have GeoJSON data in the format I provided earlier. If your data is in a different format, you may need to adjust the code accordingly.